<TITLE> Majdur Party merges with Gonosonghoti </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 14 (bdnews24.com)  Gonotantrik Majdur Party, a small left political organisation, announced its merger with Gonosonghoti Andolon, another left party, on Friday. Gonosonghoti Andolon coordinator Zonaid Saki and Gonotantrik Majdur Party president Abdus Salam announced the unification at a joint press briefing. "We've decided to work as a single organisation under the name of Gonosonghoti Andolon, as our ideology is the same," said a joint statement read out by Zonaid. The party's new central office will be announced on Saturday, he said. Elaborating the new party's goals, Zonaid said it would play a vital role in reorganising communist and revolutionary movement in the country. Taking a swipe at ruling Awami League and the main opposition BNP, he also said: "They (AL and BNP) can never protect the country's interests and improve the people's fortune." Gonotantrik Majdur Party leaders Nurul Amin, SM Amzad Hossain and Gonosonghoti Andolon leaders Abul Hasan Rubel and Shamoli Shil were present. Leaders and activists of the new party later took out a procession in the city Gonotantrik Majdur Party was formed on June 30, 1996 and Gonosonghoti Andolon on Aug 29, 2002. bdne
